	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>July 19. 1856</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Enclosed<lb/> please find duplicate of draft for<lb/> &#36;50 original of which I have<lb/> sent by mail&#44; &#38; which I hope&#44; has<lb/> duly come to hand.</p>
				<p>I have seen <persName>Mr. L. L. Dennery</persName>&#44; who<lb/> has told me&#44; that he has paid your<lb/> agent&#44; <persName>Mr Isaac Hart</persName>&#44; at <placeName>New Or&#45;<lb/>&#45;leans</placeName> up to the year <date>&#39;52</date>&#44; &#38; that<lb/> was all he owed you for&#44; as in<lb/> that year he had left <placeName>N. O.</placeName>&#44; &#38; that<lb/> he had then given you due notice of<lb/> his desire of discontinuing the Occid.<lb/>  &#8220;The Ladies United Hebrew Benevolent<lb/> Society&#8221; held their semi&#45;yearly<lb/> meeting on the <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of February</date> at<lb/> the Synagogue of Congregation<lb/> Sherith&#45;Israel.</p>
				<p>From the different reports&#44; that<lb/> were handed in by the proper of&#45;<lb/>&#45;ficers&#44; it has shown that the society<lb/> has succeeded so far&#44; since its</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>short existence in accomplishing<lb/> much good.  The many recent<lb/> calls on them for charity&#44; has exhausted<lb/> their Treasury.  By means of<lb/> a proposed Dramatic Performance<lb/> by our Jewish children for their<lb/> Benefit&#44; the society hopes soon<lb/> again to meet the many wants<lb/> of the afflicted and destitute.<lb/>  <persName>Mrs. Lichtenstein</persName> has been elected<lb/> Vice&#45;President in lieu of <persName>Mrs.<lb/> Rebecca Roggenburger</persName>&#44; who has<lb/> tendered her resignation&#59;<lb/> also an election for two more<lb/> matrons was held&#44; which resulted<lb/> in the choice of <persName>Mrs. Benjamin</persName><lb/> and <persName>Mrs. Zarinsky</persName>.</p>
				<p>Since my last one of the most<lb/> sad &#38; fatal calamity has befallen to<lb/> <persName>Mrs. S. Ottenheimer</persName> &#38; her child &#38;<lb/> <persName>Mrs. S. H. Ulmer</persName> &#38; her child&#59;<lb/> both of the Husbands reside in this<lb/> city&#44; &#38; <del>are</del> have not very long been<lb/> married.  The funeral was very<lb/> <sic>solem</sic> and imposing&#59; at least<lb/> 250 persons followed the remains<lb/> to their resting place.  <persName>Dr. Julius<lb/> Eckman</persName> delivered at the cemetery</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>an elaborate and very appropriate<lb/> discourse.  I have written out an<lb/> obituary&#44; which will explain the<lb/> circumstances of the disaster in<lb/> detail.  I should be thankful to<lb/> you for <del>the O</del> a place in the<lb/> Occident for this obituary&#44; &#38; hope<lb/> you will comply with my desire<lb/> provided the style of the writing<lb/> is fit for publication.</p>
				<p>I regret&#44; that I cannot come<lb/> up to my promise in sending you<lb/> some money with this mail.<lb/>  The principal reason of this is&#44; the<lb/> collector to whom I have given<lb/> your accounts&#44; has not been able<lb/> to attend to the same right<lb/> yet.  I have now &#36;17 on Hand&#59;<lb/> I shall endeavor to sell some Books&#44;<lb/> which in connection with some collection<lb/> for the Occident may enable me<lb/> to send you some money with<lb/> the mail of the <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of March</date>&#44; &#38;<lb/> send accompanying statement &#38;c.<lb/>  Hoping this may meet you in the<lb/> best of Health I Remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Cauffman H. Meyer</persName></p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Turn over</hi></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><persName>Mr Roggenburger</persName> &#38; family and<lb/> my brothers&#44; <persName>Mr Greenebaum</persName> &#38;<lb/> <persName>Kohland<add>&#63;</add></persName> send their kind regards<lb/> to you  <persName role="author">CHM</persName></p>
		</body>
